# Tinies (tinies.app) - Cursor Project Rules

## What This Is

Tinies is a trust-based pet services marketplace and international animal adoption platform, built for Cyprus and designed for Mediterranean expansion. It combines Rover-style local pet care booking with professional cross-border rescue animal adoption coordination. The tagline is "No matter the size."

## Tech Stack (Do Not Deviate)

- **Framework:** Next.js 14+ with App Router (NOT Pages Router)
- **Language:** TypeScript (strict mode, no `any` types)
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS v4 via `@tailwindcss/postcss` (NO tailwind.config file — config is handled via CSS). No CSS modules, no styled-components.
- **Database:** PostgreSQL via Supabase, managed through Prisma ORM
- **Auth:** Supabase Auth (email/password, Google OAuth, phone OTP via Twilio)
- **Payments:** Stripe (Checkout for owners/adopters, Connect for provider payouts)
- **File Storage:** Supabase Storage (photos, ID documents, vet records)
- **SMS:** Twilio
- **Email:** Resend with React Email templates
- **Search:** PostgreSQL full-text search + PostGIS for geospatial queries
- **Maps:** Google Maps JavaScript API
- **Hosting:** Vercel
- **Monitoring:** Sentry for errors
- **ORM:** Prisma (always use Prisma, never raw SQL unless PostGIS requires it)

## Brand & Design

All brand colors are defined as CSS variables in `src/app/globals.css` and mirrored in `design-tokens/tinies-design-tokens.css`. Always use the CSS variables, never hardcode hex values in components.

### Colors (CSS Variables)
- **Primary:** `var(--color-primary)` → `#0A8080` (teal)
- **Secondary:** `var(--color-secondary)` → `#F45D48` (coral)
- **Accent:** `var(--color-accent)` → `#0A8080` (same as primary)
- **Background:** `var(--color-background)` → `#FFFFFF` (white)
- **Surface:** `var(--color-surface)` → `#FFFFFF` (white)
- **Text:** `var(--color-text)` → `#1C1C1C` (near-black)
- **Text secondary:** `var(--color-text-secondary)` → `rgba(28, 28, 28, 0.7)`
- **Text muted:** `var(--color-text-muted)` → `rgba(28, 28, 28, 0.5)`
- **Border:** `var(--color-border)` → `rgba(10, 128, 128, 0.15)` (teal-tinted)
- **Error:** `#DC2626`
- **Success:** `#16A34A`

### Typography
- **Headings:** Georgia (serif) — warm, editorial feel
- **Body:** Roboto (sans-serif) — clean, readable
- Fonts are loaded via CSS variables `var(--font-heading)` and `var(--font-body)`

### Design Tokens
- **Border radius:** Rounded (`rounded-xl` for cards, `rounded-lg` for buttons, `rounded-full` for avatars)
- **Shadows:** Subtle, warm (`shadow-sm` default, `shadow-md` on hover)
- **Tone:** Warm, trustworthy, slightly playful but not childish. Never corporate.
- **Icons:** Lucide React

### Important: Email Templates
Some email templates in `src/lib/email/templates/` still use the old sage green `#2D6A4F`. These should be updated to use `#0A8080` (teal) to match the live site. Affected files: `booking-request.tsx`, `booking-completed.tsx`, `provider-cancelled.tsx`, `claim-reported.tsx`.

## Navigation Structure

The site uses a persistent header and footer on every page.

### Header (always visible)
- **Left:** Tinies logo (links to /)
- **Center:** Find Care (/services), Become a Provider (/for-providers), Adopt (/adopt)
- **Right (logged out):** Sign Up button, Sign In button
- **Right (logged in):** Avatar/initials dropdown menu containing: Dashboard (routes to role-specific dashboard), Messages, Settings, Log Out
- **Mobile:** Hamburger menu. If logged in, Dashboard is the first item.

### Footer (every page)
- For Pet Owners: Find Care, How It Works, Adopt
- For Providers: Become a Provider, How It Works
- For Rescues: List Your Animals, For Rescues
- Giving: Tinies Giving, Become a Guardian, Donate
- Company: About, Blog, Contact

## User Roles

The platform has five user roles. A single user account can hold multiple roles simultaneously.

1. **Pet Owner** - Searches for and books local pet care. Creates pet profiles. Leaves reviews. Browses adoptions.
2. **Service Provider** - Offers walking, sitting, boarding, drop-ins, daycare. Gets verified. Receives bookings and payouts.
3. **Rescue Organization** - Posts adoption listings. Manages local and international adoption inquiries. Coordinates with platform on logistics.
4. **International Adopter** - Based outside Cyprus. Browses adoptable animals. Submits applications. Pays adoption coordination fee.
5. **Admin** - Manages verification, disputes, adoptions pipeline, giving fund, content moderation.

## Service Types

```typescript
enum ServiceType {
  WALKING = "walking",
  SITTING = "sitting",
  BOARDING = "boarding",
  DROP_IN = "drop_in",
  DAYCARE = "daycare",
}
```

## Core Business Rules

- **Commission:** 12% of each completed booking, deducted from provider payout
- **Tinies Giving:** 10% of commission revenue is allocated to the Giving Fund for animal charities
- **Round-up donations:** Enabled by default at checkout, rounds to nearest euro, user can opt out
- **Cancellation policies:** Three tiers (Flexible, Moderate, Strict), chosen by provider
- **Provider verification:** Government ID upload, manual review by admin, must be verified to appear in search
- **Booking acceptance window:** Provider has 4 hours to accept/decline. Auto-cancel and refund if no response.
- **Payment capture:** Manual capture on booking creation. Captured when provider accepts. Cancelled if declined/expired.
- **Payouts:** Weekly via Stripe Connect. Minimum EUR 20.
- **Reviews:** 1-5 stars + text (min 20 chars). Public, permanent. Provider can respond once. Owner can edit within 48h.
- **International adoption fee:** EUR 80-150 per placement (covers coordination, not vet/transport which are passed through at cost)
- **All prices in EUR.** No multi-currency.

## Multi-Pet Pricing

Providers set a base_price and additional_pet_price per service. Booking total = base_price + (additional_pet_count * additional_pet_price). The booking flow must show the price breakdown dynamically as pets are added/removed.

## File & Folder Conventions

```
src/
  app/                    # Next.js App Router pages
    (auth)/               # Auth-related pages (login, signup, verify)
    (public)/             # Public pages (home, search, provider profiles, adopt, giving, blog)
    (dashboard)/          # Authenticated dashboard pages (owner, provider, rescue, adopter, admin)
    api/                  # API routes
  components/
    ui/                   # Reusable UI primitives (Button, Card, Input, Modal, Badge, Avatar)
    forms/                # Form components (BookingForm, ReviewForm, AdoptionApplicationForm)
    layout/               # Layout components (Header, Footer, Sidebar, Navigation)
    providers/            # Provider-specific components (ProviderCard, ProviderProfile, AvailabilityCalendar)
    adoption/             # Adoption-specific components (AnimalCard, AnimalProfile, LogisticsPipeline)
    giving/               # Giving components (RoundUpToggle, DonationPrompt, GivingDashboard)
    maps/                 # Map components (SearchMap, ServiceAreaPicker, WalkTracker)
  lib/
    supabase/             # Supabase client setup and helpers
    stripe/               # Stripe client, webhook handlers, helpers
    email/                # Email templates and sending logic
    sms/                  # Twilio SMS helpers
    utils/                # General utilities
    constants/            # App constants, enums, config
    validations/          # Zod schemas for form and API validation
  prisma/
    schema.prisma         # Database schema
    migrations/           # Prisma migrations
    seed.ts               # Seed data for development
  types/                  # Shared TypeScript type definitions
design-tokens/            # Design tokens from Refine Design (tinies-design-tokens.css)
docs/                     # Business plan and spec documents (not deployed)
design-reference/         # Competitor screenshots for visual reference (not deployed)
public/                   # Static assets (logo, favicons, OG images)
```

## Coding Patterns

- **Server Components by default.** Only use `"use client"` when the component needs interactivity (forms, toggles, maps, modals).
- **Server Actions for mutations.** Use Next.js Server Actions for form submissions and data mutations. API routes only for webhooks and external integrations (Stripe, Twilio).
- **Zod for all validation.** Define schemas in `lib/validations/`. Use on both client (form validation) and server (API/action input validation).
- **Error handling:** Try/catch in all server actions and API routes. User-facing errors as toast notifications (use Sonner). Never expose internal errors to the user.
- **Loading states:** Use Next.js `loading.tsx` for page-level loading. Use skeleton components for component-level loading. Never show a blank screen.
- **Authentication checks:** Use Supabase `getUser()` in server components. Redirect to login if unauthenticated. Check role permissions in every protected route.
- **Image handling:** All uploaded images go to Supabase Storage. Generate public URLs. Use Next.js `<Image>` component with Supabase as a configured remote pattern. Compress on upload (max 1MB, resize to max 1200px wide).
- **Dates/times:** Store all dates in UTC in the database. Display in Europe/Nicosia timezone in the UI. Use `date-fns` for formatting.
- **Currency:** Always display as "EUR X.XX" or "€X.XX". Use integers (cents) internally for all money calculations to avoid floating point issues. Display as decimals in the UI.
- **Slugs:** Auto-generate URL slugs from names (provider name, animal name, charity name). Use `slugify` library. Ensure uniqueness by appending a short random suffix if duplicate.
- **Colors:** Always use CSS variables (`var(--color-primary)`, `var(--color-secondary)`, etc.) — never hardcode hex values in components. The source of truth is `src/app/globals.css`.

## SEO Requirements

- Every public page must have: unique `<title>`, `<meta name="description">`, Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image), and Twitter Card tags.
- Provider profiles, adoption listings, charity profiles, and district landing pages must include Schema.org structured data (JSON-LD).
- Generate `sitemap.xml` dynamically from all public page routes.
- All public pages are server-rendered (no client-only rendering for SEO-critical content).
- District landing pages are auto-generated at build time: `/dog-walking/limassol`, `/pet-sitting/nicosia`, `/boarding/paphos`, etc.
- Country adoption pages: `/adopt/from-cyprus-to-uk`, `/adopt/from-cyprus-to-germany`, etc.

